<statement>
<p>Suppose enrollment in a class was 57 in the fall and 58 in the following spring.</p>
<p>It was a <input type="text" style="width:25ch" name="qn1000" id="qn1000" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 1 of 2" class="text"/> percent </p>
<p><ol style="list-style-type:upper-alpha"><li>decrease</li> 
<li>increase</li> 
</ol></p>



</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>2</li><li>B: increase</li></ul></p><p>Because 58 is bigger than 57 it is a percent increase.</p>
<p>The percent increase is <m>\displaystyle{100}{\left(\frac{{{58}-{57}}}{{57}}\right)}={100}\cdot\frac{{1}}{{57}}\approx{2}\%</m>.</p>
</solution>
